title: Canadian held for death of Canadian woman at Mexico resort
description: A Canadian man is being held in connection with the death of a Canadian woman at a resort south of Cancun

title: Mexico wanted 1st degree murder charges for Arizona rancher
description: A Mexican official says her government thought Arizona rancher George Alan Kelly should have faced first-degree murder charges for allegedly killing a Mexican migrant

title: Mexico hopes to avoid sanctions on vaquita's near extinction
description: Mexico is seeking to avoid potential trade sanctions this week for failing to stop the near-extinction of the vaquita, the world’s smallest porpoise and most endangered marine mammal

title: Alleged ‘terrorist’ attack in West Russia fuels hard-line pressure on Putin
description: Details of an alleged cross-border incursion were sketchy but Russian hardliners demanded revenge while Ukrainian officials blamed internal Russian problems.

title: Colombia tries a new solution for Pablo Escobar’s ‘cocaine hippos’
description: The four smuggled in by the drug lord in the 1970s are now more than 130. They’re devouring plant life, crowding out native animals, polluting water and threatening people.

title: Woman reported missing 31 years ago found in Puerto Rico
description: A Pennsylvania woman who went missing more than 30 years ago in a case that stumped authorities who later declared her legally dead has been found living in a nursing home in Puerto Rico

title: German Oscar film ‘All Quiet’ confronts horrors of wartime
description: “All Quiet on the Western Front,” Germany’s entry at the Academy Awards, shows the horrors of World War I from the unique perspective of the nation that triggered and lost two world wars

title: Fire at Indonesian oil depot kills 14; thousands evacuated
description: A large fire has broken out at a fuel storage depot in Indonesia’s capital, killing at least 14 people, injuring dozens of others and forcing the evacuation of thousands of nearby residents after spreading to their neighborhood

title: Why Russia and Ukraine are fighting over Bakhmut
description: If there’s one city that has come to symbolize the grinding war of attrition in Ukraine, it’s Bakhmut. It appears to be on the brink of falling to Russia.

title: Belarus sentences Nobel Peace laureate Ales Bialiatski to 10 years in jail
description: Bialiatski, a longtime human rights defender and critic of authoritarian Belarusian leader, Alexander Lukashenko, was convicted of smuggling charges, which are viewed as political retribution.

title: A decade under Maduro, migration marks Venezuelans’ lives
description: Few Venezuelans have not had their lives touched by migration over the last 10 years, when more than 7 million people left the struggling South American country

title: Aristocrat and Florida convict who ran away together charged in baby’s death
description: A search for aristocrat Constance Marten and convicted sex offender Mark Gordon ended in manslaughter charges after a baby’s body was found in Brighton, England.

title: UK couple to remain jailed after baby's remains found in bag
description: A couple whose disappearance sparked a nationwide search in England have been ordered to remain in custody after evidence presented during a court hearing revealed that the remains of an infant were found in a garden shed close to where the man and woman were finally found

title: Israel says inscription in Persian pottery shard inauthentic
description: Israel has acknowledged that an inscription in clay found in the country’s south bearing the name of Darius the Great, ruler of the ancient Persian Empire, was not authentic

title: After rescue from Mexican prison, tattooed ‘narco cat’ is going to Texas
description: Amid a slew of odd discoveries in a state Mexican prison, authorities found a tattooed Sphynx cat that belonged to Los Mexicles.

title: Heavy fighting as Russians advance in Bakhmut but Ukrainian units hold on
description: The head of Russia's Wagner mercenary group claimed the embattled city was surrounded, but a top Ukrainian general visited and soldiers said they were holding their positions.

title: Germany: Weapons found in raid on suspected extremist
description: German investigators say they seized weapons, including three hand grenades and a crossbow, from the home of a suspected anti-government extremist that was searched as part of a hate speech probe

title: Russia’s Lavrov elicits cheers and groans at Indian political dialogue
description: The audience cheered when Lavrov condemned what he called a Western double standard on Ukraine but groaned when called Russia the war’s victim during India’s Raisina Dialogue.

title: Top Moroccan soccer player charged with rape in France
description: Moroccan national team soccer player Achraf Hakimi has been placed under judicial supervision in France and has been banned from contacting his alleged victim.

title: King Charles III picks France, Germany for 1st state visits
description: King Charles III will travel to France and Germany for his first state visits since becoming monarch, underscoring Britain’s efforts to build bridges with its European neighbors

title: Army blocks Israeli rally supporting torched West Bank town
description: Protesters say the Israeli military has fired stun grenades and blocked hundreds of Israeli left-wing activists from staging a solidarity rally in a Palestinian town that was set ablaze by radical Jewish settlers earlier this week

title: 1 killed, 5 injured in bomb blast in Montenegro's capital
description: Police say one person has been killed and at least five others were injured when a hand grenade exploded at the entrance of a courthouse in Montenegro’s capital

title: Why are China’s tech leaders still disappearing if the crackdown is over?
description: Chinese tech banker Bao Fan is "assisting the government." Alibaba founder Jack Ma hops from country to country. Is China's tech crackdown really over?

title: Germany seeks to buy mothballed Swiss Leopard 2 tanks
description: The Swiss government says Germany wants to buy mothballed Leopard 2 battle tanks from Switzerland to replace tanks that Berlin and its Western allies are sending to Ukraine

title: EU countries postpone vote on combustion engine ban
description: The Swedish presidency of the European Union’s ministers’ council says the adoption by EU member countries of new carbon dioxide emission standards for cars and vans has been postponed amid opposition from Germany

title: Greece: Crash victims returned to families in closed caskets
description: Authorities in Greece say all remains recovered so far from scene of a rail disaster have been accounted for, with the death toll from the crash remaining at 57

title: Norway's leader meets Indigenous Sami as protests end
description: Norwegian Prime Minister Jonas Gahr Støre has met with Indigenous Sami reindeer herders after more than a week of protests against wind farms that activists say endanger their way of life, and has acknowledged that there are “ongoing human rights violations.”

title: Nobel laureate Bialiatski sentenced to 10 years in Belarus
description: A Belarusian court has sentenced Ales Bialiatski, Belarus’ top human rights advocate and one of the winners of the 2022 Nobel Peace Prize, to 10 years in prison

title: Faulty part from Ukraine likely cause rocket launch failure
description: The European Space Agency said Friday that an investigation into the failure of a rocket carrying two Earth observation satellites last year indicated the cause was a faulty part procured from Ukraine

title: Chinese leader Xi embarks on ‘intensive’ overhaul as he cements power
description: Xi Jinping will officially begin his precedent-breaking third term as leader of China, in a tough economic environment created partly by his zero-covid policies.

title: A year into Ukraine war, bodies dug up in once occupied town
description: The freshly exhumed remains of three men lie in black body bags on the edge of the small town’s cemetery, waiting to be taken to a morgue

title: Nordstrom to close all its Canadian stores, lay off 2,500 workers
description: All 13 Nordstrom stores in Canada are expected to be shuttered by June, the company said. Bed Bath & Beyond exited the country in February.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Biden and Scholz to meet on the war; E.U. official wants Russia to stay in G-20
description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz will meet with President Biden for a "get-down-into-the-weeds focus on the issues of Ukraine,” a U.S. official said.

title: Pakistani villages recover slowly from epic floods
description: The floods in summer 2022 were Pakistan's worst natural disaster since the country's founding in 1947.

title: A new generation of Palestinian fighters is rising up in the West Bank
description: In earlier generations, Palestinian political factions ran the brigades during street fighting against Israel. Now, teenagers and young men are calling the shots.

title: With West Bank in turmoil, new Palestinian militants emerge
description: Small groups of disillusioned young Palestinians in the West Bank are taking up guns against Israel’s open-ended occupation, defying Palestinian political leaders they scorn as Israeli collaborators

title: UN rights group says Nicaragua executed 40 people
description: A U.N. human rights groups said the government of Nicaraguan President Daniel Ortega executed at least 40 people and ordered hospitals not to treat demonstrators wounded in antigovernment protests

title: Russia’s top diplomat offers the U.S. little hope for diplomacy
description: Sergei Lavrov was a begrudgingly admired diplomatic operator, but he looks increasingly irrelevant to the future of the war in Ukraine.
